Package ast

Class Summary
Assignment Class Assignment extends Statement and takes a String variable and an Expression exp, and associates the value of the expression with the variable name in a given environment.
BinOp Class BinOp, for Binary Operation, takes in two expression and a symbol of type {+, -, *, /} indicating whether to add, subtract, multiply, or divide the two expressions, and evaluates accordingly.
Block Class Block takes a List of Statements as input and evaluates each of them.
Condition Class Condition takes two expressions and a relative operator of type {<, >, =, <>, <=, >=} and evaluates whether the boolean expression is true or false.
Expression Abstract class Expression is a template for all concrete classes containing expressions that evaluate to an integer or boolean value.
If Class If accepts a conditional and any statement, if the statement is an IF/THEN statement.
Number Class Number stores an integer value.
ProcedureCall Class ProcedureCall accepts a procedure name and a list of arguments.
ProcedureDeclaration Class ProcedureDeclaration accepts a procedure name, the statement to be evaluated inside the procedure, and a list of arguments.
Program Write a description of class Program here.
Statement Abstract class Statement is a template for all concrete classes containing statements that execute print statements, variable declarations, if statements, statement blocks, and while loops.
Variable Class Variable stores a String containing the variable name
While Class While extends Statement and takes a Condition and Statement as instance variables and executes the statement so long as the Condition is satisfied and evaluates to true.
Writeln Class Writeln accepts an expression and prints the value it evaluates to.
